I made this recipe with three 3-4 lb chickens in a Weber kettle grill for the opening night of a week long retreat and it was a smash success! I made the following changes according to other reviewers: I used a preblended spice rub and rubbed it under the skin of the chicken, in the cavity, oiled the skin with olive oil and sprinkled it over the skin and in the beer. I stuck several rosemary sprigs in each beer before putting it in the chicken. I used regular 12 oz beer and had no problems with the lid or with getting the chicken off the beer can. A pair of sturdy tongs and an oven mitt took care of that! Very, very easy recipe and a real conversation piece. Everyone wants it again for next time.

