I have been making whole chickens with beer cans for many years(it was called beer-butt chicken when I first saw the recipe), and it is good with ANY recipe. While most seem to think the secret to the succulence is the "steam," my scientist friend insists it is the hot can cooking the bird from inside out. Make sure the liquid in the can is warm/hot when you start. I use the tall Guinness cans, half full, and I have dedicated leather work gloves for removing the cans (just pick up the bird by the neck cavity, twist and pull out the can). At my house, we always cook at least two birds at a time. We call them "Dancing Chickens" because I used to tease our kids by wondering aloud what the chickens were up to inside the grill. Then I would open and close the grill real fast, so they just got a peek, and say, "Oh my, they're dancing in there!"

