This is the most awesome way ever to cook a chicken. I cooked it indirectly on a Weber kettle grill. I used hardwood natural lump charcoal.Instead of beer I used Dr. Pepper. Be sure to oil the can for ease of removal. I rubbed the chicken with zatarain's creole seasoning and curry powder. Then I drizzled orville redenbacher's popcorn butter mixed with olive oil on after about 15 mins. For a finishing glaze after one hour I mixed 1 tbsp. Grace jerk seasoning with 2 tbsp. popcorn butter, and 2 tbsp. peanut butter. Then cooked the bird for another 20 mins. and the results were incredible. I got the idea out of a recipe book devoted to beer can chicken and other unordinary ways to bbq by the same guy that wrote the bbq bible. Simply amazing!!!!!

