Rating: 4
Made this recipe several times using a bird of about 3 -4 lbs, cooking for about a little over an hour to 1 1/2. I use a gas grill, cooking indirectly (high heat to smoke chips, then medium-low for cooking), and use presoaked woodchips (hickory/mesquite), that i wrap in foil. I poke small holes in the foil and place the foil package on the heat side of the grill. It smoked fine. Place the bird on the grill, when the chips start to smoke, over the drip pan. I replace the wood chips as per taste to increase more smoke. I keep an eye on the bird and rotate it two or three times, making a crisp tasty skin all around. I have used many dry rubs, but the choice is yours; it's all good. Use a good beer like the mate from australia stated and i found using a 16 oz. works well with balancing the bird and rotating it around. This is a keeper and a great tasting, moist recipe. I have the "Stubbs" BBQ sauce, spicy, and I'm going to try that. You cant go wrong with a recipe that picky children will ask for seconds!! Remember, slow cook and low heat.

Rating: 4
