Rating: 4
I first saw this technique in the Ladies Home Journal (6/2000). I have made it several times with excellent results. The LHJ recipe told how to use a gas grill which makes cooking so much easier--place soaked wood chips in front left corner of grill and place a large disposable pan in the center of the bottom grate and add 2 cups water & replace grate. Close grill and heat grill on medium to 350 degrees. Place chickens on grill and turn off center burner if you have a triple burner grill. You can grill 3 chickens at a time. Grill for 60-70 minutes--perfect results.

